parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Starter failure can cause difficulty or inability to start the engine, which can lead to inconvenience or safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues with the windshield wiper system can cause the wipers to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to be hard to start, have an erratic idle, and die at stops, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. The strong smell of fuel can also be a fire hazard.
The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, breakdowns, and potentially even fires.
Engine failure can cause the vehicle to break down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In severe cases, engine failure can also lead to fires.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to break down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
